1. JURISDICTIONAL ACKNOWLEDGMENT (THE FLORIDA DISCLAIMER)
While this software is unencumbered, the hardware it interacts with is subject to state and federal law.

Public Domain Metadata: BearSentinel is designed solely for the analysis of unencrypted Control Channel (C-CH) telemetry. It is not an interception device for private, encrypted communications.

Mobile Restrictions: Under Florida Statute 843.16, the use of this software on any radio equipment inside a motor vehicle without a valid FCC Amateur Radio license is a first-degree misdemeanor.

Criminal Intent: Under Florida Statute 843.167, using this software to monitor or evade law enforcement during the commission of a crime is a felony.

